uso


     
 




  uso  has lost less than    year to date through september  contrast that with the price of front month futures contracts for light sweet crude  which has gained about     over the same period the uso fund isn   t the only one with this problem  the  ipath s p gsci crude oil total return
oil


     
 




  oil  fund lost about    over the same period although they have different structures  both funds buy near dated oil futures  as the contract nears expiration  the position is rolled forward to the next closest month the tracking errors stem from a current trading pattern in the oil futures market known as contango more specifically  a supply glut of crude has made oil for delivery later more expensive than oil for delivery sooner  reflecting the cost of storing the commodity and for the capital used to carry the inventory  this cost manifests when a near dated contract is sold and a new position established  the price difference can take a bite out of investors    capital    there is no way to currently track the spot price of the oil market using futures     says  john love  ceo of u s  commodity funds  which runs the uso fund  he points to the storage and capital costs as drags on return he says another of his firm   s products   u s     month oil fund
usl


     
 




  usl   buys longer dated contracts  which    mitigates    the roll costs for investors   barclays 
